{"title_page": "Moeed Yusuf", "text_new": "{{short description|Pakistani scholar and author}}\n'''Moeed W. Yusuf''' is a [[Pakistani]] scholar and author. He is currently serving as the Special Assistant to the [[Prime Minister of Pakistan]] on [[National Security Advisor (Pakistan)|National  Security Division and Strategic Policy Planning]] since 24 December 2019. He previously served as the Chairman of the Strategic Policy Planning Cell. He has also served as the associate vice president at the Asia Center at the [[United States Institute of Peace]]. He is the author of ''Brokering Peace in Nuclear Environments: U.S. Crisis Management in South Asia''.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web |title=Chairperson SPPC Bio |url=http://www.nsd.gov.pk/index.php?section=news&page=Chairman%20bio |publisher=National Security Division}}</ref>\n\nPreviously, he wrote columns for ''[[The Friday Times]]'', and had taught courses on [[political economy]] and defense economics at the [[Quaid-i-Azam University]].<ref>https://www.bu.edu/pardee/community/moeed-yusuf/</ref>\n\n==Education==\nHe holds [[Bachelors of Business Administration]] from the Shorter College; Masters and Doctor of Philosophy degrees from the [[Boston University]].<ref>https://www.bu.edu/pardee/community/moeed-yusuf/</ref>\n\n==Career==\nYusuf served as the associate vice president at the Asia Center at the [[United States Institute of Peace]].<ref>{{cite news |title=USIP dismisses false claims against Dr Moeed Yusuf |url=https://www.brecorder.com/2019/10/04/525818/ |work=Business Recorder |date=October 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 September 2019, he was appointed as Chairperson of Pakistan's Strategic Policy Planning Cell under National Security Division for a two-year period.<ref>{{cite news |title=Moeed appointed planning cell chief |url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1507417 |work=Dawn |date=September 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 December 2019, he was appointed as the Special Assistant to the [[Prime Minister of Pakistan]] on National Security Division and Strategic Policy Planning.<ref>{{cite news |title=PM appoints Dr Moeed Yusuf as special assistant on national security |url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/2124239/1-pm-appoints-dr-moeed-yusuf-special-assistant-national-security/ |work=The Express Tribune |date=December 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Work==\n* ''Brokering Peace in Nuclear Environments: US Crisis Management in South Asia'' (2018)<ref>{{cite news |title=Book Review: Brokering peace in nuclear environments |url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1800932/1-book-review-brokering-peace-nuclear-environments/ |work=The Express Tribune |date=September 12, 2018}}</ref>\n*''South Asia 2060: Envisioning Regional Futures'' (co-edited) (2013)<ref name=\":0\" />\n*''Getting it Right in Afghanistan'' (co-edited) (2013)<ref name=\":0\" />\ncnicfuefjekwfbnjkewh f\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Pakistan-bio-stub}}\n\n{{Authority Control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Yusuf, Moeed}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Pakistani writers]]\n[[Category:Imran Khan administration]]\n[[Category:Boston University alumni]]\n[[Category:Pakistani columnists]]\n[[Category:Quaid-i-Azam University faculty]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Pakistani scholar and author}}\n'''Moeed W. Yusuf''' is a [[Pakistani]] scholar and author. He is currently serving as the Special Assistant to the [[Prime Minister of Pakistan]] on [[National Security Advisor (Pakistan)|National  Security Division and Strategic Policy Planning]] since 24 December 2019. He previously served as the Chairman of the Strategic Policy Planning Cell. He has also served as the associate vice president at the Asia Center at the [[United States Institute of Peace]]. He is the author of ''Brokering Peace in Nuclear Environments: U.S. Crisis Management in South Asia''.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web |title=Chairperson SPPC Bio |url=http://www.nsd.gov.pk/index.php?section=news&page=Chairman%20bio |publisher=National Security Division}}</ref>\n\nPreviously, he wrote columns for ''[[The Friday Times]]'', and had taught courses on [[political economy]] and defense economics at the [[Quaid-i-Azam University]].<ref>https://www.bu.edu/pardee/community/moeed-yusuf/</ref>\n\n==Education==\nHe holds [[Bachelors of Business Administration]] from the Shorter College; Masters and Doctor of Philosophy degrees from the [[Boston University]].<ref>https://www.bu.edu/pardee/community/moeed-yusuf/</ref>\n\n==Career==\nYusuf served as the associate vice president at the Asia Center at the [[United States Institute of Peace]].<ref>{{cite news |title=USIP dismisses false claims against Dr Moeed Yusuf |url=https://www.brecorder.com/2019/10/04/525818/ |work=Business Recorder |date=October 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 September 2019, he was appointed as Chairperson of Pakistan's Strategic Policy Planning Cell under National Security Division for a two-year period.<ref>{{cite news |title=Moeed appointed planning cell chief |url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1507417 |work=Dawn |date=September 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 December 2019, he was appointed as the Special Assistant to the [[Prime Minister of Pakistan]] on National Security Division and Strategic Policy Planning.<ref>{{cite news |title=PM appoints Dr Moeed Yusuf as special assistant on national security |url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/2124239/1-pm-appoints-dr-moeed-yusuf-special-assistant-national-security/ |work=The Express Tribune |date=December 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Work==\n* ''Brokering Peace in Nuclear Environments: US Crisis Management in South Asia'' (2018)<ref>{{cite news |title=Book Review: Brokering peace in nuclear environments |url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1800932/1-book-review-brokering-peace-nuclear-environments/ |work=The Express Tribune |date=September 12, 2018}}</ref>\n*''South Asia 2060: Envisioning Regional Futures'' (co-edited) (2013)<ref name=\":0\" />\n*''Getting it Right in Afghanistan'' (co-edited) (2013)<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Pakistan-bio-stub}}